 demo_path: ["/#constellation-frame", "/topics/software/#interactive-codeblocks", "/topics/software/pretext/"]
}

^["stream"]{
 >>[2026-04-09 21:06] observe - The site currently has no committed SVG assets; the most illustration-like surface on the home page is still a raster image with layered PNG overlays in `#constellation-frame`.
 >>[2026-04-09 21:06] observe - Existing interactive surfaces already point toward the need for SVG hosts: interactive codeblocks on the software page, the Pretext lab's projection surfaces, and the land-cluster / constellation material all want diagrams that can stay linked to semantics.
 >>[2026-04-09 21:06] observe - `spw-component-semantics.js` and `style.css` already provide orthogonal kind/form/role/liminality/selection axes, which means SVG should enter as another host surface in the same grammar rather than as a separate mini-framework.
 >>[2026-04-09 21:06] decide - Plan around a four-part split: SVG surface taxonomy, inline-versus-external asset rules, host/runtime contracts, and an authoring ladder for future Spw-backed components and pages.
 >>[2026-04-09 21:06] decide - Keep the runtime dependency explicit: mobile runtime doctrine, prefix/postfix symmetry, and brace pivots come first; SVG should intensify the surface model, not fork it.
 >>[2026-04-09 21:06] taste - Wonder should come from layers becoming structurally legible on inspection, not from perpetual animated SVG decoration.
 >>[2026-04-09] style - The constellation frame is the only place the site has made a visual vocabulary commitment: sparse points, relational arcs, depth through proximity and layering rather than perspective. New SVG should acknowledge that grammar before departing from it — or explicitly name the departure as a deliberate choice.
 >>[2026-04-09] observe - The site's primary relational content is already named: operator families, surface-to-surface bridges, domain adjacencies, spirit phase sequences. Illustrations that make those visible would feel native. Illustrations that don't reference that material would feel borrowed.
 >>[2026-04-09] style - Diagrammatic warmth on this site likely means: legible relation over decorative form, operator color tokens carrying semantic hierarchy, whitespace proportioned for inspection, and enough label residue that a diagram could become an inspectable surface rather than a static image.
 >>[2026-04-09] observe - SVG is a style development moment: the first authored illustration will establish whether this site's visual language is sparse, relational, annotated, geometric, or something else — log that choice explicitly when it is made.
}

^["open"]{
 ?[taxonomy]: "What is the cleanest boundary between a static illustration, an addressable illustration, a widget, and a region-owning interactive component?"
 ?[hosting]: "Which SVG surfaces should stay external files and which should be inlined into HTML for inspectability and local pivots?"
 ?[semantics]: "How should SVG subtargets inherit or declare kind, form, role, liminality, and selection without becoming verbose markup noise?"
 ?[touch]: "What is the mobile-first inspect gesture or focus path for subtargets inside a bounded SVG host?"
 ?[pivots]: "Which SVG interactions should count as local pivots into deeper structure rather than navigations or generic overlays?"
 ?[authoring]: "What is the smallest host contract that future Spw-backed components can target without requiring a build step?"
 ?[fallback]: "How should a scripted SVG widget degrade when JavaScript or motion features are unavailable?"
 ?[wonder]: "Which layers of revelation feel magical because they expose relation, not because they add motion?"
 ?[visual_vocabulary]: "What does the site's diagram language look like fully developed — sparse and relational, geometric and formal, annotated, or something the constellation frame implies but hasn't proven?"
 ?[relation_priority]: "Which relationships should be made visually legible first — operator family trees, surface-to-surface bridges, domain adjacencies, or spirit phase sequences?"
 ?[warmth_definition]: "Define diagrammatic warmth specifically for this site: is it label generosity, color tenderness, proportional whitespace, or the feeling of a mind mapping its own territory?"
 ?[illustration_voice]: "What quality distinguishes an illustration that belongs to this sensibility — what does it share with the written copy and the operator atlas pages?"
 ?[first_illustration_log]: "When the first authored SVG illustration is committed, what style decision should be explicitly logged in this stream?"
}

^["commits"]{
 ~[1]: "#[svg] - capture the SVG surface integration plan and distilled taxonomy"
 ~[2]: ".[svg] - formalize SVG host semantics, authoring rules, and brace-aware interaction contracts"
 ~[3]: "&[svg] - add shared SVG host runtime and containment primitives"
 ~[4]: "&[widgets] - integrate first SVG widgets and inspectable illustrations into site surfaces"
 ~[5]: "![svg] - verify touch, keyboard, reduced-motion, and fallback behavior"
}

